# Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js blog project with TypeScript and Tailwind CSS.

## Key Directories
- `src/` - Main source code directory
  - `app/` - Next.js 13+ app directory
  - `components/` - React components
    - `icons/` - SVG icon components
    - `ui/` - Reusable UI components
  - `contexts/` - React context providers
  - `lib/` - Utility functions and shared code

## Configuration Files
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - Tailwind CSS configuration
- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration
- [postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs) - PostCSS configuration

## Theme System
The project uses a custom theme system with:
- Dark/light mode support
- Custom color variables
- View transitions for theme switching

## Component Guidelines
- Icons are implemented as React components in `src/components/icons/`
- UI components are in `src/components/ui/`
- All components use TypeScript and support className props

